The paper combines deep learning and probabilistic programming, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on deep neural networks and their use in inference suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The use of probabilistic programming languages suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category. The paper also deals with approximate inference, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks for inference could also place the paper in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on combining different methods to improve efficiency suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
